HEADWORD: Tethys
<hw>Te"thys</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ an
oyster, or <?/ a kind of ascidian.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
genus of a large naked mollusks having a very large, broad, fringed
cephalic disk, and branched dorsal gills. Some of the species become a
foot long and are brilliantly colored.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

